# Copilot Instructions

## Project Guidelines
- Authorization is intended to be enforced at endpoint level using a custom HasPermission attribute, which should accept only a permission argument and be reusable across controllers/endpoints (workspace, space, task, etc.), allowing service methods to assume permission checks have already passed.
- The app domain is ClickUp-like and hierarchical: Workspace -> Space -> Tasks/Notes, with analytics across this hierarchy.
- User requires task/feature validation to align with already-verified permission/authorization behavior and frontend view constraints.
- The userId passed to workspace service methods is guaranteed non-null by the authenticated endpoint pipeline.
- InviteMember.request.email is already validated upstream in request validation, so null/empty checks in service are not required by current project flow.
- SpacesController should be accessible only to users in the Member role; other roles (including admin if not a member) should not access it.
- A Space dashboard endpoint is not required; the dashboard should exist only at the Workspace level.
- Responses should be based only on the current project context (`AI_genda_API2`) and project files for future questions.
- Implement subtask endpoints/contracts/services and logical test scenarios, but do not generate unit test files.
- Use one class per file when creating or refactoring code.
- Keep the current implementation as-is first, review/revise the design, and only apply code changes after explicit approval.

## User Interface Guidelines
- Profile UI will not allow direct email editing in the main profile form; email changes are handled through a dedicated change-email flow.
- ChangePassword user null-forgiving is not to be treated as an issue.
- UploadAvatar relies on a validator and should not be flagged as an issue.
- UserNotFounded/UserIsDeleted consistency should not be flagged unless behavior changes.
- Analyze UI screens before applying code changes; wait for the next set of images/requirements before proceeding.

## Notes Feature Guidelines
- Voice notes must be stored as audio files; transcription text is optional and should not be treated as the primary stored content.